===Etymology 4===
{{zh-forms|s=绷|t2=綳|alt=崩,嘣}}
Some compounds are attested at least since Ming dynasty. May be related to {{zh-l|綁}} (in {{zh-m|緊綁綁}}) used in Yuan era plays.

Mandarin dialects generally use reduplicated {{zh-m|邦}} instead (e.g. in {{zh-m|硬邦邦}}), also spelled {{zh-m|梆}} or {{zh-m|幫}}. See also Hokkien {{zh-m|迸|piàng}} (in {{zh-m|硬迸迸|ngē-piàng-piàng}}, {{zh-m|緊迸迸|kín-piàng-piàng}}, etc.).

;''very; terribly''
:Same as above, but without reduplication. Used prepositively in a few collocations. Most Standard Chinese dictionaries nominally assign the ''bèng'' reading to this sense and merge it with Etymology 3, but Northeastern Mandarin and Xiang dialects where it is actually used have the dark level tone for it (corresponding to Beijing Mandarin ''bēng''). See also {{zh-m|迸|bèng|''(dialectal Mandarin)'' very [[dry]]; [[crisp]]; [[brittle]]}}.

